)\n#[[Eleonora Dalpr\u00e0]] (ITA), EV Bozen Eagles, 11 points (4+7)\n#[[Cindy Debuquet]] (FRA), HC Neuilly-sur-Marne, 8 points (4+4)\n#[[Lili Pint\u00e9r]] (HUN), UTE Marilyn Budapest, 6 points (3+3)\n\n==Round 2==\nThe second round was played 5-7 December 2014. The winner of each group progressed to the finals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://webarchive.iihf.com/home-of-hockey/news/news-singleview/?tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=9231&cHash=64bbba647b9dfd112e68a8615d476a31|title=EWCC enters next stage|last=|first=|date=2014-04-12|website=IIHF News|publisher=[[International Ice Hockey Federation]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-18}}</ref>\n\n===Group E===\nHost City: [[Nizhny Novgorod]], [[Russia]]\n\n'''Standings'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"70%\"\n|- style=\"font-weight:bold; background-color:#eeffff;\" align=\"center\" |\n| width=\"5%\" | \n| width=\"30%\" | Team\n| width=\"5%\" | GP\n| width=\"5%\" | Pts\n| width=\"5%\" | W\n| width=\"5%\" | L\n| width=\"5%\" | GF:GA\n| width=\"5%\" | diff\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 1. || align=\"left\" |{{flagicon|RUS|#}} '''[[SKIF Nizhny Novgorod]]'''\n| 3 || 9 || 3 || 0 || 13:{{0}}1 || +12\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 2. || align=\"left\" |{{flagicon|AUT|#}} [[EHV Sabres Wien|EHV Sabres Vienna]]\n| 3 || 6 || 2 || 1 || {{0}}9:{{0}}4 || +5\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 3. || align=\"left\" |{{flagicon|CZE|#}} [[SK Karvin\u00e1]]\n| 3 || 3 || 1 || 2 ||{{0}}7:{{0}}7 || 0\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 4. || align=\"left\" |{{flagicon|SVK|#}} [[HK Poprad]]\n| 3 || 0 || 0 || 3 ||{{0}}3:20 || -17\n|}\n'''Top Scorers'''\n\n#[[Olga Sosina]] (RUS), SKIF Nizhny Novgorod, 6 points (1+5)\n#[[Pia Pren]] (SLO), EHV Sabres Vienna, 5 points (4+1)\n#[[Maria Pechnikova]] (RUS), SKIF Nizhny Novgorod, 5 points (2+3)\n#[[Aneta Ledlova]] (CZE), SK Karvin\u00e1, 4 points (2+2)\n#[[Anna Meixner]] (AUT), EHV Sabres Vienna, 3 points (3+0)\n\n'''Group E Best Players Selected by the Directorate'''\n\n*Best Goaltender: [[Meeri R\u00e4is\u00e4nen]] (FIN